meaning.definition: a place of study or training in a special field.
meaning.example: a police academy

meaning.definition: a society or institution of distinguished scholars and artists or scientists that aims to promote and maintain standards in its particular field.
meaning.example: the Royal Academy of Arts

meaning.definition: complete lack of inhibition or restraint.
meaning.example: she sings and sways with total abandon

meaning.definition: (of a building or other area) provide lodging or sufficient space for.
meaning.example: the cottages accommodate up to six people

meaning.definition: fit in with the wishes or needs of.
meaning.example: any language must accommodate new concepts

meaning.definition: give or grant someone (power, status, or recognition).
meaning.example: the powers accorded to the head of state

meaning.definition: (of a concept or fact) be harmonious or consistent with.
meaning.example: his views accorded well with those of Merivale

meaning.definition: an official agreement or treaty.
meaning.example: opposition groups refused to sign the accord

meaning.definition: a value or principle which is regarded as universally valid or which may be viewed without relation to other things.
meaning.example: good and evil are presented as absolutes

meaning.definition: an absurd state of affairs.
meaning.example: the incidents that followed bordered on the absurd

meaning.definition: deviating from what is normal or usual, typically in a way that is undesirable or worrying.
meaning.example: the illness is recognizable from the patient's abnormal behaviour

meaning.definition: a convenient arrangement; a settlement or compromise.
meaning.example: the prime minister was seeking an accommodation with Labour

meaning.definition: the process of adapting or adjusting to someone or something.
meaning.example: accommodation to a separate political entity was not possible

meaning.definition: the process or work of keeping financial accounts.
meaning.example: an investigation into suspected false accounting

meaning.definition: a musical part which supports or partners an instrument, voice, or group.
meaning.example: she sang to a guitar accompaniment

meaning.definition: something that supplements or complements something else.
meaning.example: these biscuits are a lovely accompaniment to tea

meaning.definition: the improper use of something.
meaning.example: alcohol abuse

meaning.definition: cruel and violent treatment of a person or animal.
meaning.example: a black eye and other signs of physical abuse

meaning.definition: insulting and offensive language.
meaning.example: waving his fists and hurling abuse at the driver

meaning.definition: (especially of a vehicle) begin to move more quickly.
meaning.example: the car accelerated towards her

meaning.definition: existing in thought or as an idea but not having a physical or concrete existence.
meaning.example: abstract concepts such as love or beauty

meaning.definition: relating to or denoting art that does not attempt to represent external reality, but rather seeks to achieve its effect using shapes, colours, and textures.
meaning.example: abstract pictures

meaning.definition: consider something theoretically or separately from (something else).
meaning.example: to abstract science and religion from their historical context can lead to anachronism

meaning.definition: extract or remove (something).
meaning.example: applications to abstract more water from streams

meaning.definition: make a written summary of (an article or book).
meaning.example: staff who abstract material for an online database

meaning.definition: a summary of the contents of a book, article, or speech.
meaning.example: an abstract of her speech

meaning.definition: an abstract work of art.
meaning.example: a big unframed abstract

meaning.definition: a teacher or scholar in a university or other institute of higher education.
meaning.example: the EU offers grants to academics for research on approved projects

meaning.definition: the quality or state of being ridiculous or wildly unreasonable.
meaning.example: Duncan laughed at the absurdity of the situation

meaning.definition: a substance with particular chemical properties including turning litmus red, neutralizing alkalis, and dissolving some metals; typically, a corrosive or sour-tasting liquid of this kind.
meaning.example: trees were exposed to mixtures of heavy metals, acids, and overdoses of nutrients

meaning.definition: repeal or do away with (a law, right, or formal agreement).
meaning.example: a proposal to abrogate temporarily the right to strike

meaning.definition: accept or admit the existence or truth of.
meaning.example: the plight of the refugees was acknowledged by the authorities

meaning.definition: recognize the importance or quality of.
meaning.example: the art world has begun to acknowledge his genius

meaning.definition: show that one has noticed or recognized (someone) by making a gesture or greeting.
meaning.example: she refused to acknowledge my presence

meaning.definition: (especially of information, measurements, or predictions) correct in all details; exact.
meaning.example: accurate information about the illness is essential

meaning.definition: (with reference to a weapon, missile, or shot) capable of or successful in reaching the intended target.
meaning.example: reliable, accurate rifles

meaning.definition: the action or process of adapting or being adapted.
meaning.example: the adaptation of teaching strategy to meet students' needs

meaning.definition: gather together or acquire an increasing number or quantity of.
meaning.example: investigators have yet to accumulate enough evidence

meaning.definition: make (something) active or operative.
meaning.example: fumes from cooking are enough to activate the alarm

meaning.definition: a person whose job is to keep or inspect financial accounts.

in a manner involving great or constant activity actively toward the goal of opening his own restaurant> Synonyms actively, assiduously, diligently, industriously, laboriously. Related Words energetically, vigorously; indefatigably, tirelessly. Near Antonyms lifelessly, sleepily.
a report or description of an event or experience.
meaning.example: a detailed account of what has been achieved

meaning.definition: a record or statement of financial expenditure and receipts relating to a particular period or purpose.
meaning.example: the barman was doing his accounts

meaning.definition: an arrangement by which a body holds funds on behalf of a client or supplies goods or services to them on credit.
meaning.example: a bank account

meaning.definition: importance.
meaning.example: money was of no account to her

meaning.definition: an interpretation or rendering of a piece of music.
meaning.example: a lively account of Offenbach's score

meaning.definition: consider or regard in a specified way.
meaning.example: her visit could not be accounted a success

meaning.definition: an arrangement by which a user is given personalized access to a computer, website, or application, typically by entering a username and password.
meaning.example: we've reset your password to prevent others from accessing your account

meaning.definition: (in solo whist) a bid by which a player undertakes to make nine or more tricks.
a very large quantity of something.
meaning.example: the tropical island boasts an abundance of wildlife

meaning.definition: existing or available in large quantities; plentiful.
meaning.example: there was abundant evidence to support the theory

meaning.definition: (of a benefit or sum of money) be received by someone in regular or increasing amounts over time.
meaning.example: financial benefits will accrue from restructuring

meaning.definition: go somewhere with (someone) as a companion or escort.
meaning.example: the two sisters were to accompany us to London

meaning.definition: be present or occur at the same time as (something else).
meaning.example: the illness is often accompanied by nausea

meaning.definition: play a musical accompaniment for.
meaning.example: he would play his violin, and Mother used to accompany him on our organ

meaning.definition: alter or move (something) slightly in order to achieve the desired fit, appearance, or result.
meaning.example: he smoothed his hair and adjusted his tie

meaning.definition: assess (loss or damages) when settling an insurance claim.
meaning.example: the insurance agent may have the responsibility of adjusting small losses

meaning.definition: failing to produce the intended result.
meaning.example: the rebel officers who led the abortive coup were shot

meaning.definition: make someone aware of or familiar with.
meaning.example: new staff should be acquainted with fire exit routes

meaning.definition: referring to a crossword answer which reads horizontally.
meaning.example: 19 across

meaning.definition: from one side to the other of (a place, area, etc.).
meaning.example: I ran across the street

meaning.definition: expressing position or orientation.
meaning.example: they lived across the street from one another

meaning.definition: used to express a concession or recognition that something is the case.
meaning.example: admittedly, the salary was not wonderful

meaning.definition: buy or obtain (an asset or object) for oneself.
meaning.example: I managed to acquire all the books I needed

meaning.definition: learn or develop (a skill, habit, or quality).
meaning.example: I've acquired a taste for whisky

meaning.definition: happening by chance, unintentionally, or unexpectedly.
meaning.example: a verdict of accidental death

meaning.definition: incidental; subsidiary.
meaning.example: the location is accidental and contributes nothing to the poem
